        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Valid2StartProcess",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to determine the next billing period based on the most recent executed billing period from a specific table. It calculates the next billing period and checks if there is an entry in another table for this calculated period. The result is returned through an output parameter."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving basic SQL operations such as variable declarations, simple SELECT queries, date calculations, and conditional logic. It does not involve complex joins, subqueries, or intricate business logic."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
